@peter

Yep! That’s why I’ve been making my own oatmilk lately. It doesn’t stay emulsified as well, but I just shake it up when I use it. I’m a blender, whir for about 70 seconds: 1/2 c oats, 2 T maple syrup, 1/4 salt, 1/2 t vanilla, 3 c water. Strain it through a sieve twice, to get rid of most of the solids. 

But for this recipe, I’d probably just use water.
